Comments: I asked how to move forward getting our tax exempt status and was given an email address that just bounced back

The winds of change are upon us. As times evolve, so must our ways of communicating and working. You must now collaborate with independent writers, embracing fresh perspectives and ideas. This is not a threat to tradition; instead, it's an invitation to innovate and adapt. We must recognize that today's children will soon inherit the world we leave behind. It's imperative we prepare them for the unexpected twists and turns that lie ahead, equipping them with the knowledge and adaptability they'll need. We should not fear change but embrace it. By accepting and adapting to changes sooner rather than later, we ensure a smoother transition for everyone involved. The fabric of our future is being woven today, and we must ensure our children are ready to uphold the balance in the ever-evolving landscape. Thank you for being a part of this journey. Together, let's create a future where the next generation thrives. Thx Dimitri Gilles
I needed the help of customer service...the young lady that helped me was very patient and she solved my problem!  A very satisfied customer here.

I have not received my son's order that I placed over a month ago and was told to contact the teacher. Then, if the teacher can't find it, I was told to have the teacher contact you all. I feel like you are asking a lot for me to be the go-between between you and the teacher. Can't you just ship this to me?

My daughter's school is still using the codes to locate their class. Her actual teacher isn't in the pre-populated list. I'm being told her teacher needs to set up an account but this is false because she sent the scholastic flier home with the code so she obviously has an account. I hate that you took the code spot away because now you are out a sale. I can't buy because I can't link it to her class and her classroom has to suffer because they won't get the credit. It's a shame.
Let me pay the amount without having to call back yet again. I'm trying to pay for the book I ordered for my son but apparently it's hard to be honest.

I would like to have multiple options for books that are for $2.00. You had this in previous years so I am not sure what happened but now I am unable to afford extra books for the kids in my classroom. The representative said that you guys no longer provided multiple options for books that are $2.00.
My account had an $11 credit and she ignored my question, not applying the credit in any way.
Alert teachers each day about the parent orders until it is submitted.   I ordered books and have bo idea when they are coming.

This was the first time I used the QR code to access your website. Prior to this, the teacher handed out the flyer, you made your choices, wrote out a check, and sent the order with your check back to the teacher. I liked the idea of the app, because I don’t have to worry about lost orders, money, or checks.   However, I found your app difficult to navigate if you are not technically inclined. When you enter the grade level, it would be beneficial if the latest flyer came up. It took me quite a while to find it, and I am technically savvy. I used to have a classroom account until I retired.   When I signed in as a parent/family member, I kept getting routed to my old account. That has been resolved thanks to the customer service rep. When I finally got to shop, I had to search for the current flyer.

I purchased a e-gift card. Applied it to my daughter's account. When she went to get her books it said she has a zero balance. I went back to the gift card info  to see if maybe it never transfered and it said my card was invalid. My daughter was very upset and I am angry. Where is my $20?
I have received no response other than this request to complete a survey. My question has not been addressed.

I would like to have my order shipped to my house address. I would like to set my order due date . One of my students wanted to send in their order and not order online. They didn't  end up ordering. One of my student's order was put on another teacher's order. It makes it harder for me to have the orders go to my school  because some days the order arrives after our school closes and I have to go back to my school  and pick up my order that is left while knows where. I like to set my order due date because I know what works best for my students and their  families.
Wish we didn't have to contact scholastic to get tax refunded from teacher orders.

Give me more options to make the change a little easier for us older teachers! lol I just do not like the automatic orders that go out on their own. If I want to order books for my class using points I cannot until the next due date or use any bonus items because it automatically puts all the orders in. SO I would like the chance to submit my orders with time to input my points. I do not like this change at all.
My order was submitted automatically and Janice helped me add the books that was free worth $10.
She was fine. I am just frustrated that I cannot set my own due dates.

Due to the poor area I work in, I have purchased dollar books for my class on a monthly basis or bundles that were offered like 10 books for $10 etc.  I am sad to see these go.  I also will no longer be able to afford to buy my class books on a monthly basis. Bring dollar books back or bundles with the same title like, 5 for 5, 8 for 8 or 10 for 10.

The only thing - which has nothing to do with why I contacted Scholastic before - I'm wondering if I'm doing something wrong.  I have entered part of my classes book order but I did not get finished.  When I went back, I cannot find the current order I was working on and I believe last year, I could pull it up if I didn't finish it at one time.  Can you clarify/help me with this?  Thanks so much and have a blessed day!
Just want to be able to set my own due dates! Please bring back set your own due dates!
a bit more information about the timing of my refund from my account
Everything went smoothly and my question was answered and resolved.

I think it was resolved in the best way it could be. It concerns a book I ordered, All Thirteen, which I am unhappy with. There is nothing wrong with the book. It's just not what I expected. It is big and heavy with small print and not many pictures. Not a book that I would imagine elementary students looking at much less reading. It is probably my fault for not researching it more. I used 600 bonus points so it is not even a matter of sending it back to get a refund. As I said, the problem is not really your fault. There is nothing wrong with the book. It's just not something that I can use.
Not sure if I ever got an answer.
The person on the chat was prompt and very informative.  I am completely new to Scholastic and your representative provided excellent customer service.  Thank you!
She was very helpful. She answered my questions thoroughly and timely.

There is no solution to new system with QR code system for parents to order books online. Will I still earn points if I order for students as a teacher? New QR code will not work for schools in low income neighborhoods where parents do not speak English or are tech savvy.
Make it so when orders are put in you do not need to call for invoice with taxes removed.  When you have record of our tax exempt  status.
I was missing the extra, extra bonus at the beginning of the school year.  There isn't as much incentive to start the year as in the past.

I have called twice about the same thing.  I think the customer service person did the best they could but the issue hasn't been resolved yet.  Part of it is mail I believe.  However in the past we have always received our scholastic book order fliers with plenty of time.  At this point we still haven't received our September fliers and we are halfway through September.  I also haven't yet received my Scholastic Big World booklets for September.  I received October but not September.  The first person I spoke with said I should receive our book order fliers last Thursday (September 14) by noon.  Friday we still hadn't received them so I called again and they said I should get them but in case they would mail out a second set.  If that takes 7-10 business days we won't get them until September 26+/- and by then we are almost at the end of the month.  Hopefully next month will go more smoothly and we get them out in a timely manner.

I do not like how the system auto submits parent orders. I have more orders to add to it and have now lost out on bonus points and free books. If this is the future of book clubs, I will no longer solicit to my families.
I did not realize the paper order blank was no longer available.

The response was quick and very nice.  I just wish we could get the paper flyers like before.  I do understand the reason why, but I liked being able to have the students look through and pick their favorites in class (and not using tech).

I had no problems with the representative.  However I am still frustrated that there are not a lot of affordable book options for parents and teachers to purchase for students.  Scholastic has taken away nearly every affordable option to purchase books for my students, with the exception of the $2 book of the month.  I understand that prices need to be adjusted for inflation,  however removing the options is unfortunate.  Would it be possible to have a $2 book of the week?  Or bundle packs of the same book with 10 quantity for $20?  Please give us more options!
I tried calling, but there was no answer. That was frustrating.

I'm not sure my question was completely understood.   It is still not resolved on my end.   It was suggested I contact my bank to question the two pending charges when only 1 purchase was made, but the two charges are for two different transactions for two different amounts.   I attached copies but apparently they were not looked at.

I replied and tried to see if they will fix the problem.  As of right now, it is still not resolved.  My family order was submitted without my teacher order (although my credit card was on file).  My teacher order would have pushed the total order over $100 in order to earn the extra 500 bonus points.  I tried to submit my teacher order AFTER Scholastic submitted my order for me (which I did not care for them to do).  When I tried to submit my order so that it would be combined, there was a $6.95 shipping charge added to my $2 book.  IF Scholastic would NOT have submitted my order for me, I would have had an order over $100, with my extra 500 bonus points, I would have gotten my teacher order in, and I would have been able to get my item that I wanted with my bonus points.
Is Scholastic deliberately making life harder?
I used the online chat.  The response of the agent was quick and efficient.

I was disappointed to hear that you no longer offer the $1 book of the week. Customer Service was great in helping me find out this information, but it is sad news. My class loves having a new book every month from my fundraising. It is unfortunate because we will not longer be able to afford book of the month at $2 per book as I cannot get enough money from friends and family to get a book for each of my 25 students every month. I am hoping for scholastic to bring back book of the week for $1 next year. I wasn't aware of the change until now and will have to pay out of my own pocket for half of the cost for each set of books for my class every month in order to keep my promise to them. Without the $1 books I will no longer be able to do this amazing program I have done for years and giving a home library to students.
My family order was automatically submitted and I was not able to spend the $10 on books for the month.
My person did a great job answering all of my questions.

Nothing wrong with the agent.  I think it's a terrible corporate decision not to allow teachers to set a due date. My due date is almost a month from now.  Silly for me to send out flyers. You'll be getting less orders. Allow teachers to change their class date!!
I was credited for shipping, but I think I had more credit on my account than what was being shown because of a previous email I received.

I like how parents had the option to pay with check and how the flyers were in the past.   I also don't like the fact I can't set my own return date for book orderes.     I did it so parents could be able to order in between pay days.      Not everyone has a bank account or credit card to pay for money with.

You could have not changed the ordering process to families having to order online. I'm very upset over this change that we were supposedly informed of, but I never received anything about it. My scoring has nothing to do with the representative. She was kind and helpful. My upset is with the company and the unfair way they changed things.

You answered my questions~Not happy with the answers...Not sure I like how/where Scholastic is headed~we'll know before the end of the school year...too much has been changed with the book orders. I am not happy not being able to set my own book order deadline. It is not an "extra thing" for me to do.  I liked the book orders the way they have been in the past. It feels like you've "dumbed down" the orders~TOO SIMPLIFIED of an order form. I am also NOT happy that you have taken away the gift card option of Target, etc from the Bonus Point section. I have been teaching for 40 years. I have Many books and sometimes, I like to utilize the gift cards to purchase things that can't be obtained from Scholastic Books.
Thank you for having the chat option available. It was quick, easy, and helped me place my online order. Thanks again!
My email was responded to quickly and took care of the issue that I had inquired about.
your new policy of setting the due date and not allowing teachers to submit orders is bonkers! I almost don't want to use your service.

I am disappointed in the changes in the bonus catalog. I purchase  Christmas gifts for many of my students. I have been saving to gather gift cards to help with this.  I called, but they guy I spoke to was not listening to what I said. He kept giving me canned answers.
My chat always timed out before I could finish typing
Sherri was fabulous and took the time to help me with my order.  She is an asset to Scholastic!!
Very frustrating that we can no longer add Parent Orders in when they give us a paper order

The experience was fine, but it was disappointing to know that you only offer a book of the month in English, but you don't have plans to offer one in Spanish. It will be very helpful for teachers whose students received Language Arts instruction in Spanish.
I did not contact a representative, but have attempted to sign up for scholastic news/science spin 1st grade. I did not get my code to activate my subscription -it has been much longer than 48 hours.

I was surprised at the change in format with only online orders this year. Also, being a teacher at a small parochial school, it's hard to reach golden apple status with small class sizes.  I've been a teacher for 35 years...maybe when a teacher reaches a certain milestone of years teaching, they could be part of the golden apple club  ;) Have a great day!

As a very long time supporter of Scholastic book clubs, I am disheartened that the bonus point options have been so drastically cut. I was saving them up from last year to purchase an electronic (the desk top apple computer) and am very close to having the points. The bonus point options are not enticing for me to put the effort into supporting the book club if it is going to continue as such. I reach out to family and friends to sponsor a student and make sure every kid in my class gets a book with each order. I would love to continue this, but the book club incentives need to value the teachers that put forth the extra effort.

My question was answered, so in all fairness, the service was fine. I am finding it harder and harder to use Scholastic - it all seems much less friendly than in the past. Books are more expensive, my families could get them more cost effectively elsewhere. As a teacher, I used to love giving my students books. I can no longer afford that as most books are more than $1 X 22 students. The website has become increasingly more difficult to use, and now I can't even pick order due dates that meet my needs. I'm very disappointed.
I feel that my feedback was brushed off.
I was looking at the bonus catalog and I am very disappointed that you did away with gift cards for redemption.
Not sure I am wondering why I cannot change my due date for my scholastic family book orders.

I voiced a concern about the book club changes.  I do not like the fact that you took the control away from  me in setting due dates and not knowing who has ordered what when.  The answer well that is the way it is now is not a sufficient answer to my dissatisfaction.

Make the site less confusing.  I recently had to send you an email because when I logged onto my teacher account, I couldn’t find the order that I knew a parent had placed.  I received a reply that walked me through the steps so that I could find the order. But how stupid is it for your system to not inform me easily that a parent had placed an order.  Please fix that!  Also, I do not ever want you to automatically place a parent order.  I like to get my bonus books, order books for the classroom, etc while I have free shipping.  I would like to be removed from ever having an order auto order.  I’m fully capable of placing my own order (as long as I can find it on your convoluted site!).
I am disappointed that scholastic no longer has a ready made editable letter home.  I am not happy about the set due dates..

I gave a very detailed first message that included my order number, customer number, and item number. I ordered two of a book and only received one. The lady told me I only ordered one. I had the packaging slip that showed I ordered two and my online order. She then looked up my order online. She said she saw I ordered two books. She asked, "Did you want to order two books?" I feel like she wasn't listening/reading my concerns. She did end up sending another copy.
Made book club changes more evident.
It is frustrating that the live chat gets closed out if I didn't respond within a few minutes. I need assistance, but am also running the fair so it is hard to respond immediately.

I do not like that we cannot set our own order due date anymore. The response was to make it easier on teachers, but honestly it is not making it easier at all!  Please bring back the due date setting!
My question was answered promptly, but I am super disappointed that you discontinued the birthday coupon books, the dollar book and 10 for 10 book deals.

I have been accumulating my bonus points with the plan to order a laptop or desktop.  I am VERY disappointed to see that those electronic items are no longer available in the bonus catalog.  Will they be available again in the near future?  I am hoping so.
I want to set my own due date.
The chat representative was helpful and efficient in helping me.

You have changed your ordering policy and it makes it difficult to order for teachers that need to place orders using cash. I work with a poor students and your new credit card ordering system is excluding them.

While the situation was resolved, it did not correct the problem for me. The ability to change due dates is something I would like to have in case this happens again. Sometimes I intend to have one date but life gets in the way and I don't get information out to parents and I've always been able to change the due date so I could get the information out to them. Now I am unable to do this and this is a stress to me as a teacher. I liked it better when it was flexible.

I do not understand how you deciding on my due date helps me at all. You have no clue when I need the book orders back by. I should be able to make that decision myself. Give teachers the ability to set their own due date
There was nothing that could have been done to improve the overall experience.
Not decide due dates for orders
I am still waiting for my flyers to arrive.  I don't know why I didn't receive them this year.
I don't like the way the book clubs are now not within the teacher control to be able to set dates or to print labels.

I am very dissatisfied that I can no longer offer booklets to our parents with the school code and have them place their orders. As a director the new system where I now have to take this on is not convenient.
Explained more about setting up a teacher's account, how to get ready for my students to place an order.
I don’t like the fact that I cannot choose a due date for my parents. A parent order was placed without me having the option to order along with it to get the free shipping.

The person I was talking with couldn't help me much because Scholastic had apparently made the decision to set book order due dates for everyone. And the teacher cannot adjust them.... Let us set our own book order due dates.
READS coupon not available for families who can't access computer to order books

I am very disappointed that you have decided to make "fixed" due dates for orders.  Teachers should not be held to these dates.  This does not make it easier for teachers, nor does it "eliminate a step" as the person I spoke with claimed.  It actually adds a step to the ordering process because we now have to send a note or email to parents letting them know the online date is not correct.  Having a set date might make it easier for Scholastic, but it certainly does not make it easier for teachers and should not be touted as if it does.

I was looking for apple products to use my bonus points on.  I reached out to customer service to ask why all apple products were gone and why the items were so limited to use bonus points on.  The chat rep responded with a rather unprofessional and nonsense answer that the individual "was low on the totem pole.  So low on the totem pole, basically underground. "  It was such a bizarre response to my question.

consider adding more affordable books for families Return to your previous program to include some inexpensive options so more kids can take part in ordering. Also the flyers are way to long. It is fine to combine grade levels but there is too much included.
I feel as if my concerns weren't addressed.
Allow me to adjust my own dates for completing orders.

Eliminate the imposed DUE DATE or at least allow educators to modify. I have used Scholastic for years and will continue to be a patron.  However, as previously mentioned, I am not nor will I ever agree with the imposed DUE DATE policy.

Yes, I needed tax exempt status on an order I had placed using a PO. I was contacted by Chris  Case ID 9921521 with this response "I do see that your school has a tax exemption certificate on file. Please wait until you receive notification that your order has shipped and then submit your request for a new invoice. This will allow time for the order's bill to be processed and we will be happy to remove the tax at that time and send you a new invoice. I apologize for any inconvenience." This is very frustrating, Tax Exempt should be applied automatically to the order. I should not have to make several contacts with your company to receive this deduction. It should be automatic.

There’s no reason why I should not have been in your system. My parents could not order right away and I was never told of anything I needed to do. I do not like the new flyer or the prices.  One of the best parts of the scholastic book order was that it has affordable books.  I can’t believe how expensive everything was.  I don’t expect many orders this year and I can’t blame the parents for that.

As a teacher, I am disappointed in the new policies that we just found out about.  They started before our school year and so we were not prepared with our budgets to make the necessary changes in ordering our classroom sets.  We often receive donations to purchase classroom sets that we give to our students at the end of each month.  We were not prepared to meet the new Scholastic imposed deadlines.  Also, all the prices have gone up quite a bit.  Unfortunately, we understand this is a nation wide issue, but this year's donations we sought are not going to cover the new expenses.  Last year the books we purchased were around $2.00 a book.  This year we cannot find things for our Kindergarteners that are less than $4.00 a book.  We will struggle to provide these to our students at these costs.  We work in a Title 1 school, where most of our students come from poverty.
I would love to be able to edit the due date. I don’t always want the orders due when the preset date is, and it causes confusion with parents.
Not sure how my profile was changed from educator to parent.  I had to have that resolved and it was

Our school is listed twice:  Edgerton Public and District 581 Edgerton.  Some teachers are in one and some are in the other. I requested that Scholastic just have one Edgerton Public.  The first person I talked to said she fixed it, but she didn’t.  The second person I got disconnected from. The third person I messaged said only an administrator could make changes.  So, my administrator contacted Scholastic… and there’s still two Edgerton Publics with some teachers under one and some teachers under the other.  The problem with this is that parents get confused and can’t find the correct teacher when they want to place an online order.
I lost my Access Code.  Customer Service helped me within minutes via chat and I was all set!  Thank you!

I don’t care for the new automatic due date for classroom flyers. I want to be able to set the due dates around what is going on in my classroom. Also, I have found that parents forget about entering the order if it is set for mor than 2-3 weeks. A month is too long. I appreciated the very quick response to my question.
I'm just not pleased with the changes that you've made for this school year.

The check that I sent in hasn’t been processed. The woman said it may take 6-8 weeks. I want to purchase book for my class for September. Also, no longer have $1 books makes this difficult. I will not be doing it again. I do not like your new ordering method either.

I reached out anout the changes to the ordering program and how I can enter my teacher point certificates and coupons.  The person did not understand what was being asked.  Also I would like to know how I can share my disappointment with the changes to the program- it is not teacher friendly and will cause me not to order and unfortunately not be able to use the program!!

The agent I interacted with was helpful and responded to my question.  Overall I was not happy because I did not care for the answer.  Some of the changes that have been made have taken choice away from me.  I do not like that I cannot set my own date and I do not really need you to submit my orders.  I am sure you are doing this based on the experience you have had with others, but I personally do not like this change.

My rating in no way reflects on the customer service representative, I am just very disappointed in the decision to do away with printed catalogues, I feel this will lead to a huge dip in sales and excitement in my classroom.

Customer service was quick and informative. Unfortunately, the $1 Book of the Week specials from this past year are no longer provided and I can no longer afford to purchase books for my class. Please consider bringing back the highlighted book of the week for the specialized program like last year!

I would like the option to set my own due date. It is easier for me and for families when it can match homework and other due dates. I received an email stating “action required.” When I went to submit my student orders and add my own, the order was already processed. Maybe a better message would be “Your order will be submitted tomorrow. Please review and place additional orders.”

The rep I chatted with online was very apologetic about my dissatisfaction with your new online only ordering policy.  So nothing could have been done to improve it because that is not able to be changed.  I was contacting you in hopes of there being a different way to order. Nothing could have been done to resolve it because it's not able to be changed.  I was contacting you in hopes of there being an order form put on the flyer so parents could have sent their order in easier.  I did find out I am able to enter parents' orders for those who are not able to do that so I appreciate knowing that.
Answered with more detail the first time Not a fan of the new flyers or way of ordering.

This has nothing to do with your customer service but I’m super bummed that you did away with the Judy Newman $1 book of the week. It was a great way to get books into the hands of all my first graders in the low income district I teach in. I really hope you will bring them back!
I greatly dislike the new system that limits the flyers and orders along with lessening bonus points. I will be less likely to eagerly share orders with families.

I needed to ship my most recent order to my home because I was creating a surprise for my classroom and I was not allowed to do this. the person helping was not helpful either. Teachers need to be able to send orders to their home. some schools are not accepting of teachers using scholastic and we should not have to be subject to dealing with that.
I dont think I reached out to you
Nothing I guess. Overall, I am pretty displeased with all the changes since last year. I am debating if this month is my last class order or not.
Many of my students need the paper order forms which they return to me so I can order their books for them.  This is no longer an option offered by Scholastic.

I don't like the  new policy regarding deadlines. Teachers should be able to have the flexibility of setting due dates and not have parents log on to see a conflicting date.  I am not happy about only offering online.   I prefer to have book club boxes sent to my home, because of our unique school situation. (We do not have mail delivery. Staff must drive to the local PO with authorization, then pass boxes on to custodian before we can get our books.) That can take an extra week. At home, it is at my door in a shot. I have a long time relationship with Scholastic. My customer # was 000 xxx- xxxx. I even pushed orders during Covid. I am not sure if this year will be my last w/ Scholastic. 'Sad to say it, but true.
Respond I do not know how to any longer get to my teacher page everything has changed.
Allow teachers to once again place their own due dates

1) Allow teachers to override the "preset" date.  I did not pass out the "4th & 5th Grade Back to School 2023" paper flyers because it was too close to the  "preset" date. 2) Have the printed order form on the paper flyer. 1) Teachers not being able to override the "preset" date.   2) Missing the printed order form on the paper flyer.

I do not like that I cannot attach a student's name to the order, and I was charged tax for the orders.  These orders are being placed through a school, which should be tax exempt. I will consider no longer placing orders with Scholastic.
I received a reply quickly and it answered my questions. Thank you!!!!
This company is always reliable and helpful.  Thank you.
Happy to report that the problem that In was having was resolved quickly.  Much appreciated!
No one could find our order for $400.00 worth of books ordered 5 weeks ago, apparently it got lost in the mail, but everyone that I talked to said it could be a different dept. NOT HELPFUL!

I had a parent who could not find my name on the list to connect her order to the class. She spent over $150 on her order and contacted me about how to make sure I gets points to spend in our class. But because she already ordered, I was told that there was nothing that could be done. I think that SOMEONE on your end somewhere, could apply points for a $150 purchase, seeing as this makes a huge difference to my classroom. I was told nothing could be done. I provided the order # & amount, but still nothing. I'd love it if someone went above and beyond for a customer of 9 years who has spent thousands of dollars on Scholastic books.

I felt like my concern was dismissed & not resolved. I need a birthday book coupon book for my preschool classrooms, this is my 11th year teaching & it’s part of my bday gift to the kids that they get to pick their own (up to $5) book and I was told you have them anymore?? What should I do now? Parents of returning siblings are expecting that & the kids will be disappointed. Why do you not offer them anymore?
I wish I had a better answer on why the book flyers were not delivered to our school at the start of the school year this year.  I'm not saying it's a Scholastic only issue.
When I tried to enter my points that I was given in an email online it said I my order wasn't big enough. It was $190.00.
Allow teachers to set their own due dates I think teachers should have the option to have a set due date or choose their own
The ability to purchase a $1.00 has been eliminated & there is no "Dollar Store" available.

NOTHING I will say that I do not like the changesyou have make to your magazines.  I feel like you are forcing us to just do online orders.  I was not able to edit the date on the parent letter and there is no order form for parents to fill out on the paper form.  I
Notify teachers of big changes like doing  away with the early childhood flyer option.
did not receive flyers. she just said they were sent. ask person in school who does mail. didn't even verify address or anything

for the past 15 years, I've started the year by 'selling' Scholastic book clubs because of the the 10,000 bonus point offer. I use that to supply my students who cannot afford to buy books themselves with books. This is not available this year, which totally hamstrings my efforts to get books into the hands of my most needy students. I am VERY disappointed. Last year, my order totaled more than $1000. I will not be using Scholastic Book Clubs unless the bonus point incentives are improved.

I am very disappointed in the new system.   The paper copy of the book order is terrible.  Why waste the time printing it if it is so minimal.  Not worth giving out to students.  Also, the idea that everything is on line is a very poor choice.  Yes it is a great option for many. But, our school has many many  families without internet access-  yes the is true.
